ARCH LINUX INSTALLATION SCRIPT BY NICOLAS MARGOSSIAN
1) run livecd arch linux installation
2) create/format partitions
3) download (clone) scripts from github.com/NicoMargo/ArchLinuxScripts to /root
4) go inside download folder (cd ArchLinuxScripts)
5) execute first script (./script1.sh)
6) create user (useradd -m NameUser -G wheel)
7) set zsh to new user (chsh -s /bin/zsh user &&)
8) mount efi partition (mount /dev/sdXX /boot/EFI) XX represent the partition letter and number
9) arch-chroot -u NewUserCreated:NewUserCreated /mnt ./script3.sh